<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Understanding the Body's Fluid Control Center</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #2563eb;
            --secondary: #3b82f6;
            --accent: #60a5fa;
            --dark: #1e293b;
            --light: #f8fafc;
            --success: #10b981;
        }
        
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.5;
            color: var(--dark);
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        .card {
            background: white;
            max-width: 600px;
            width: 100%;
            border-radius: 16px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
            padding: 24px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary);
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-top: 0;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
            padding-bottom: 12px;
        }

        p.intro {
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            color: #475569;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
        }

        .system-container {
            background: var(--light);
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            position: relative;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .status-bar {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            background: #e2e8f0;
            padding: 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .status-indicator {
            padding: 4px 12px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .status-hydrated {
            background: #d1fae5;
            color: #065f46;
        }

        .status-dehydrated {
            background: #fee2e2;
            color: #991b1b;
        }

        .toggle-btn {
            background: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            font-weight: 600;
            cursor: pointer;
            width: 100%;
            transition: background 0.2s;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

        .toggle-btn:hover {
            background: #1d4ed8;
        }

        .step-box {
            background: white;
            border-left: 4px solid #cbd5e1;
            padding: 12px 16px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
            transition: all 0.4s ease;
            opacity: 0.7;
            transform: scale(0.98);
        }

        .step-box.active {
            border-left-color: var(--secondary);
            opacity: 1;
            transform: scale(1);
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        }

        .step-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--dark);
            margin-bottom: 4px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .step-desc {
            font-size: 0.92rem;
            color: #475569;
        }

        .legs-connection {
            background: #f0fdf4;
            border: 1px solid #bbf7d0;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 16px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            display: none;
        }

        .legs-connection h3 {
            margin-top: 0;
            color: #166534;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .legs-connection ul {
            margin: 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
            font-size: 0.92rem;
            color: #1e293b;
        }

        .legs-connection li {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="card">
    <h1>The Body's Fluid Control Center</h1>
    <p class="intro">Think of your body's fluid management system (RAAS) as an automated emergency backup pump. Toggle the system below to see how it reacts to dehydration.</p>
    
    <div class="system-container">
        <div class="status-bar">
            <span>Body Status:</span>
            <span id="statusIndicator" class="status-indicator status-hydrated">Perfect Fluid Levels</span>
        </div>

        <div id="step1" class="step-box">
            <div class="step-title">💧 1. The Scout (Renin)</div>
            <div class="step-desc" id="desc1">The kidneys monitor blood flow constantly. Currently, everything is smooth and stable.</div>
        </div>

        <div id="step2" class="step-box">
            <div class="step-title">⚡ 2. The Enforcer (Angiotensin)</div>
            <div class="step-desc" id="desc2">Blood vessels are naturally relaxed. Blood moves easily around the entire body.</div>
        </div>

        <div id="step3" class="step-box">
            <div class="step-title">🔒 3. The Vault (Aldosterone)</div>
            <div class="step-desc" id="desc3">The kidneys allow natural fluid elimination because the body is well-stocked on water.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <button id="toggleBtn" class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleSystem()">Simulate Dehydration</button>

    <div id="legsConnection" class="legs-connection">
        <h3>🎯 How This Connects to Restless Legs</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Narrowed Circulation:</strong> Because the system tightens blood vessels to keep your blood pressure stable, blood flow to your resting leg muscles slows down in the evening.</li>
            <li><strong>Linger Tension:</strong> Slower circulation means natural muscle waste takes slightly longer to clear away, which can create that "crawling" or tight sensation.</li>
            <li><strong>Salt Shifting:</strong> While the system works hard to trap fluids, it can temporarily upset the delicate balance of potassium and magnesium your muscles need to relax.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    let isDehydrated = false;

    function toggleSystem() {
        isDehydrated = !isDehydrated;
        
        const statusIndicator = document.getElementById('statusIndicator');
        const toggleBtn = document.getElementById('toggleBtn');
        const legsConnection = document.getElementById('legsConnection');
        
        const s1 = document.getElementById('step1');
        const s2 = document.getElementById('step2');
        const s3 = document.getElementById('step3');
        
        const d1 = document.getElementById('desc1');
        const d2 = document.getElementById('desc2');
        const d3 = document.getElementById('desc3');

        if (isDehydrated) {
            statusIndicator.textContent = "Low Fluids (Dehydrated)";
            statusIndicator.className = "status-indicator status-dehydrated";
            toggleBtn.textContent = "Rehydrate Body";
            legsConnection.style.display = "block";

            // Activate Steps with customized text
            s1.classList.add('active');
            d1.innerHTML = "<strong>Alarm sounded!</strong> Fluid levels drop, lowering blood pressure. The kidneys immediately release a chemical scout called <em>Renin</em> to start a rescue mission.";
            
            setTimeout(() => {
                s2.classList.add('active');
                d2.innerHTML = "<strong>Vessels tighten!</strong> Renin triggers a powerful chemical called <em>Angiotensin</em>. It narrows blood vessels like a tight rubber band to protect your vital organs, and triggers thirst.";
            }, 400);

            setTimeout(() => {
                s3.classList.add('active');
                d3.innerHTML = "<strong>Lockdown mode!</strong> The system releases a hormone called <em>Aldosterone</em>, telling the kidneys to slam the brakes on fluid loss and aggressively trap salt and water.";
            }, 800);

        } else {
            statusIndicator.textContent = "Perfect Fluid Levels";
            statusIndicator.className = "status-indicator status-hydrated";
            toggleBtn.textContent = "Simulate Dehydration";
            legsConnection.style.display = "none";

            // Reset Steps
            s1.classList.remove('active');
            s2.classList.remove('active');
            s3.classList.remove('active');
            
            d1.textContent = "The kidneys monitor blood flow constantly. Currently, everything is smooth and stable.";
            d2.textContent = "Blood vessels are naturally relaxed. Blood moves easily around the entire body.";
            d3.textContent = "The kidneys allow natural fluid elimination because the body is well-stocked on water.";
        }
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>
